@startuml Data Flow Diagram
title Data Flow - FLEXT Plugin System

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline

actor "Plugin Developer" as Developer
participant "CLI/API" as Interface
participant "FlextPluginApi" as API
participant "FlextPluginPlatform" as Platform
participant "Discovery Service" as Discovery
participant "Plugin Registry" as Registry
participant "Security Validator" as Security
participant "Plugin Loader" as Loader
participant "Plugin Cache" as Cache
participant "Plugin Instance" as Plugin
participant "Monitoring" as Monitoring
database "File System" as Filesystem

== Plugin Development ==
Developer -> Interface: Create plugin code
Interface -> Filesystem: Save plugin files

== Plugin Discovery ==
API -> Platform: discover_plugins(paths)
Platform -> Discovery: discover_plugins(paths)
Discovery -> Filesystem: scan directories
Filesystem --> Discovery: plugin files list
Discovery -> Registry: validate and store metadata
Registry --> Discovery: plugin metadata stored

== Plugin Loading ==
API -> Platform: load_plugin(name)
Platform -> Loader: load_plugin(name)
Loader -> Registry: get plugin metadata
Registry --> Loader: plugin configuration
Loader -> Security: validate plugin security
Security --> Loader: security approval
Loader -> Filesystem: load plugin code
Filesystem --> Loader: plugin source code
Loader -> Cache: cache compiled plugin
Cache --> Loader: cached plugin stored
Loader --> Platform: plugin instance
Platform --> API: loaded plugin

== Plugin Execution ==
API -> Platform: execute_plugin(name, context)
Platform -> Plugin: execute(context)
Plugin -> Monitoring: record execution start
Plugin -> Filesystem: read/write data (if needed)
Filesystem --> Plugin: data access
Plugin -> Monitoring: record execution metrics
Plugin --> Platform: execution result
Platform -> Registry: update execution history
Registry --> Platform: history updated
Platform --> API: execution result

== Hot Reload ==
Platform -> Discovery: watch directories
Discovery -> Filesystem: file system monitoring
Filesystem --> Discovery: file change detected
Discovery -> Loader: reload plugin
Loader -> Cache: invalidate cache
Cache --> Loader: cache cleared
Loader -> Platform: plugin reloaded
Platform -> Monitoring: reload event

== Monitoring and Metrics ==
Plugin -> Monitoring: execution metrics
Platform -> Monitoring: system metrics
Security -> Monitoring: security events
Monitoring -> API: expose metrics endpoint

== Error Handling ==
Plugin -> Platform: execution error
Platform -> Monitoring: error logged
Platform -> API: error result
API -> Interface: error response

@enduml